   Get variables in list item using: 
        @foreach(var item in Model.[Name]) { 
            // Put code here 
        }

   Get resource data with language steps:
        - Define ResourceKey in /Core/Enums/ResourceKeyCollection.cs
        - Named Key:
            + Common: is the key often used. Ex: Search, Read_More, Detail,...
            + Specified Location: is the key exist at some specified place. Ex: Contact_Address, News_Others,...
            + Validation Key: Ask Backend developers to get more information.
        - Define library at the head of this View: @using MainProject.Core.Enums
        - Using this code in View: @Html.GetResource(ResourceKeyCollection.[Name])

    Get Form register
        - Split form html into Sub-View
        - Using: @Html.Partial("[Name]", new [Model]()) Ex: @Html.Partial("_Subscribe", new MainProject.SBussiness.LandingPage.Models.Home.SubscribeModel())

    Get Introduction list items:
        - Define library at the head of this View: @using MainProject.Core
